message: "If you use this framework, cite the essay as the canonical source of the method. Cite the CLI release only when you depend on the reference implementation."
title: "Robopsychology: A Framework for Behavioral Diagnostics of AI Systems"
abstract: >-
  Robopsychology is a framework for diagnosing the behavior of large language
  model systems from the outside. It separates any observed output into three
  layers — model tendencies, runtime/host pressure, and conversation effects —
  and offers a sixteen-prompt toolkit, a five-rule operating protocol, and a
  nine-step diagnostic ratchet that makes performed transparency expensive and
  genuine transparency cheap. This repository hosts the framework documents,
  modular prompt cards, no-CLI templates, reproducible validation cases, a
  paper scaffold, and the `robopsych` reference CLI implementation.
